    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to Erasmus of Rotterdam (Brussels, 25 June
                    1534)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p>1. He is briefly responding to his letter of 22 April, lest he misses the
                            courier. Thomas More is said to still be in captivity, and John Fisher
                            is not safe, either. Erasmus’ health worries him, he would be happy if
                            he returned. According to Erasmus, the marquess will not do anything
                            against Michaël Hillen von Hoochstraaten; but Erasmus is afraid of the
                            monks, too. Oláh does not understand what he should be afraid of, only
                            the Lutherans are to be feared. 2. There is no need to thank for his
                            services for Erasmus. Oláh will go where fate calls him, but he really
                            wishes he were home, his brothers, friends, and others are looking
                            forward to welcoming him back home, but the situation is quite turbulent
                            there now.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p>Nicolai Olai ad Desyderium Erasmum Roterodamum. </p>
                <p>[1.] <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I">Salutem plurimam!</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II"/>
                    </app> Litteras, quas ad me XXII. Aprilis dedisti,<note type="critic">Ep.
                        482.</note><ref>/o:olahus.tei.15340422_1</ref> XII. Maii praeteriti accepi.
                    Nuntium hunc nolui sine meis litteris ad te proficisci. Ad litteras igitur tuas
                    breviter accipe. </p>
                <p>Angliae <persName>regis</persName><note type="critic">King Henry
                        VIII.</note>
                    <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I">res</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II">actiones</rdg>
                    </app> scribis te ex parte credere. At credes brevi in omnibus.
                        <persName>Morus</persName><note type="critic">Thomas More.</note> adhuc
                    captus esse dicitur cum <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I">Rofensi</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II">Roffensi</rdg>
                    </app>,<note type="critic">John Fisher.</note> non sine periculo, ut aiunt.
                    Valetudo tua est mihi <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I">molestissima</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II">ingratissima</rdg>
                    </app>, cuperem, ut bene valeres et redires.
                        <persName>Marchionem</persName><note type="critic">William van den
                        Werwe.</note> nihil facturum scribis <persName>Hillenio</persName>.<note
                        type="critic">Michaël Hillen von Hoochstraaten</note> Times <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I">monachos</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II">funigeros</rdg>
                    </app>. Si factus es tam timidus, et in <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I">eo</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II">hoc timore</rdg>
                    </app> constans esse <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I">pergis</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II">perges</rdg>
                    </app>, non facile tibi <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I">hunc</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II"><del corresp="Olahus">hinc</del><add corresp="Olahus"
                                type="corr">eum</add></rdg>
                    </app> exhaurire possum <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I">timorem</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II"/>
                    </app>, nihil tamen video, quod <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I">tibi hic</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II">hic tibi</rdg>
                    </app> magnopere esset timendum. Si <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I">vereris</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II">times</rdg>
                    </app> obtrectationes hominum nostrae aetatis, ab <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I">his</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II">eis</rdg>
                    </app> nec tu, nec alii, dum vivunt, liberi esse possunt. Hic parum, istic ubi <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I">nunc</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II"/>
                    </app> es <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I">existimo plurimum</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II">plurimum existimo</rdg>
                    </app> tibi <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I">posse (quod absit)</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II"/>
                    </app> imminere mali, si praesentium temporum conditionem <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I">consideraveris</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II">consideraris</rdg>
                    </app>. Cave igitur milites <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I">Luteranos</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II">Lutheranos</rdg>
                    </app>, quorum fortasse rabies ad ea usque loca, ubi <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I">nunc agis, (di malum hoc prohibeant) brevi</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II">es, di id prohibeant</rdg>
                    </app> penetrabunt. </p>
                <p>[2.] Meum in te officium, de quo scribis, tale est, ut nihil <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I">a te aliud</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II">aliud a te</rdg>
                    </app> exigat, quam testimonium tui erga me amoris et <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I">utque</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II">ut</rdg>
                    </app> Olaum tuum ames. Reditum meum in Hungariam scribis tibi incommodum
                    futurum, sive huc redeas, sive non. Quocumque me fata vocent, tuum, quem nosti, <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I">omnibus in locis</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II"/>
                    </app> habebis Olaum. Utinam, mi Erasme, salvis rebus reverti possem, nihil eo
                    esset mihi iucundius. Patria, <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I">fratres, amici et alii </lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II">amici, fratres</rdg>
                    </app>
                    <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I"/>
                        <rdg wit="#II">et</rdg>
                    </app> necessitudine <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I">intima</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II"/>
                    </app> mihi iuncti me hortantur, ut redeam. Sed id quam commode nunc facere
                    possim, rebus non modo Hungaricis <milestone unit="pb"/>et publicis et meis quoque privatis, sed etiam aliis regiis, non <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I">sine magno malo</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II">minimum</rdg>
                    </app> turbatis, vix <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I">statuere statis</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II">statis statuere</rdg>
                    </app> possum, huius rei causa tempori serviendum esse arbitror. Apud
                        <persName>reginam</persName> meam, ducem <persName>Arscoti</persName>,<note
                        type="critic">Philippe II de Croÿ.</note>
                    <persName>Panormitanum</persName><note type="critic">Jean II Carondelet.</note>
                    fui, tibi vice epistolae et quae voluisti, eis retuli. Vale et me, ut soles,
                    ama. </p>
                <p><placeName>Bruxellae</placeName> 25. Iunii 1534.</p>
                <p>
                    <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I">Tuus, ut nosti. Olaus etc.</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II"/>
                    </app>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <app>
                        <lem wit="#CE #I">Excellentissimo viro domino Erasmo Roterodamo, sacrae
                            theologiae doctori etc., domino et amico praecipuo et
                            observandissimo.</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II"/>
                    </app>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
